        "timestamp": 1773059466,
        "contenuto_esteso": "To display this content from YouTube, you must enable advertisement tracking and audience measurement. One of your browser extensions seems to be blocking the video player from loading. To watch this content, you may need to disable it on this site. Europe rallies around Cyprus after Iranian strikes Europe Issued on: 09/03/2026 - 13:31 French President Emmanuel Macron travelled to Cyprus on March 9, days after dispatching a warship to the east Mediterranean island nation, where a Shahed drone struck a British air base on its southern coast last week during the Iran war. The goal is to show the 'French military might' to defend partners in the region, among other messages, says FRANCE 24's Kethevane Gorjestani. Donald Trump seeks Kyiv's help in defending against Iranian drones 06/03/2026 Middle East US and Middle East countries seek Ukraine's support in drone protection 05/03/2026 Europe Trump threatens to cut off trade with Spain over Iran war refusal 03/03/2026 Europe France to boost nuclear arsenal, could deploy atomic weapons to European allies 02/03/2026 Europe Europe 'exposed to the consequences' of US-Israel's conflict with Iran 02/03/2026 Europe Europe 'very likely' to get dragged into conflict after UK base in Cyprus hit 02/03/2026 Europe Middle East war to have economic and military fallouts for Europe 02/03/2026 Europe Milan tram derails and slams into a building, killing two people 28/02/2026 Europe 'Security, dilemma over Greenland have enhanced urgency' for EU referendum in Iceland 26/02/2026 Europe"
